    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>https://xxou.github.io/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://xxou.github.io/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Enjoy the mind flow! &amp;#x1f3b6;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My name is Xiaxian Ou (欧夏娴). I am a biostatistics master student in &lt;a href=&#34;https://sph.emory.edu/departments/bios/index.html&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Department of Biostatistics and Bioinformatics&lt;/a&gt; at Emory University, working under the supervision of &lt;a href=&#34;https://raziehnabi.com/&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Razieh Nabi&lt;/a&gt; on causal path-specific effect (PSE) analysis. My research focuses on the multiply robust estimators derived from efficient influence functions and their applications in health disparities.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Before starting my master’s program, I earned my bachelor’s degree in Medicine from &lt;a href=&#34;https://english.pku.edu.cn/&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Peking University&lt;/a&gt;. Shifting my career from medicine to biostatistics is not an easy way, but I believe it is the right way.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Papers</title>
      <link>https://xxou.github.io/papers/</link>
